10/21/83  send_mail request:  write, w

Syntax:  w path {-control_args}


Function:  writes the printed representation of the message to the end
of an existing segment.


Arguments:
path
   is the pathname of the segment to which the message is written.  The
   suffix "mail" is added if necessary.   


Control arguments:
-extend
   writes the message at the end of the segment if there is already
   data present in the segment.  (Default)
-truncate, -tc
   truncates the segment before writing the message.


Notes:
If the segment identified by the path argument does not exist, it will
be created automatically.
